values:
So I'm sitting here waiting for my phone to ring to tell me that I've got the job at AG, and then I thought- Hmmm, I know that one of my referee's only works part-time so I should check when she's in- just in case AG have left her a message to call her back. Guess what? She's on Annual Leave for 2 weeks and her voice mail doesn't say that!
So I stressed out, called the AG department and gave them the name and number of another referee!

STRESS!!!!
Glad I checked though- hope they see this as me being attentive and eager!

Finger's crossed!

I'm as sick as a dog.
There's so much I want to update on, but can't be bothered.
Waiting for the stupid temp to arrive so I can go home to bed yet again.
Damn fruit juice and yummy food is at the house and I'm going back to my apartment.
Crap...

Have a job interview tomorrow, so hopefully I'm well enough for that.
Want to write about how fantastic our engagement party was on Saturday night, but I feel like I shouldn't due to the fact that my grandmother passed away last night...

Only 1 sleep left and I'm in Melbourne!

Apparently mum has gone absolutely crazy with this whole engagement thing- all I wanted was a small get together so that Matt could meet my whole family before we got married. Instead, they've been cleaning the backyard for 3 weekends- they've even bleached the concrete! There's a pink colour theme, a cake, decorations- the whole kit and Caboodle! Crazy! And I don't have anything to wear! Guess I'll have to pop out to Highpoint on Saturday morning!

Yesterday was an awesome day. I cried when they started bringing the furniture in! It's a real home now!
I stayed there last night and we were sitting on the couch down stairs, and I was telling Matt that I could see a puppy running around on the tiles and even a baby somewhere along the track!

I got a call yesterday to say that I've been short-listed for a job in the public service! APS3 Personal Assistant for the Attorney General's department! Finally- after 6 applications since June 1st, someone has finally called me! The group interview is today at 3pm so another early day for me!

Other than that- it's only 170 days til the wedding! It's that website "the bride's diary" that keeps me informed! That site's so funny- I love reading the forum's- I can't believe some of the girls are so excited that they've hit 499 days til their wedding when they started 650 days ago! And these are the girls who have already gotten their dresses, are having their 3rd and 4th make-up/hair trials!

I never want to clean again.
Spent 10 hours cleaning our new house on the weekend.
I thought the builder was meant to have cleaners come in and do it, but apparently I'm wrong when it's a private builder.
So I've wiped down every surface, cleaned every window, every mirror and vacuumed every inch of that house. I feel like my arm should be in a sling- that's how sore my shoulder is.

Haven't really spent much time with my Matthew this weekend. Dropped the girls off at their school "disco" on Friday night. The hall was all dark with fluro lights and they were given glow in the dark necklaces, and the DJ was setting up. Soooo cute!
Saturday morning began with Matthew getting rid of lice from Hannah's hair. Lovely. Amazing how paranoid you get and how itchy your scalp becomes! Then watched her play soccer then went straight out to the house to do stage one of cleaning. Matt was outside laying down that gravel stuff you need before you pave. I had the girls helping me wipe down skirting boards, clean mirrors etc. They were actually really helpful. Ended up almost falling asleep at 7.30pm so decided to go home to bed.
Sunday morning I got to play "dancing mum". Got Hannah ready for her Irish Dancing Competition (4th and 5th place). Was dreading it because it was meant to go from 9.30-11.30 and Matt was leaving at 10 to play soccer. Only reason I was dreading it was because I knew Emma was going to be there but I kinda assumed her support network (both her parents, and her sister and brother-in-law). Overall it wasn't too bad- it finished at 11 and only Emma was there. Went back to the house after that and vacuumed all day. The house has one of those wall vacuum cleaners. They are absolutely awesome! The suction on those are great! Got the girls to pack their stuff into boxes last night, so at least that's done now.
Very exciting that I finally get to spend some one-on-one time with my Matthew tonight.

They stuffed up!
Miscommunication apparently!

So we're still getting our house today!!!!

Stupid f*cking bank.

They have screwed us around with this homeloan so many f*cking times.

First we were told that we had preapproval on a certain amount.
Then when we found a house in that price range that we liked and applied for the house, they didn't approve the amount.
We found another place (which is the place we're buying now) which was cheaper.
They come back and say they screwed up and we have the loan approved for the previous house.
We liked the 2nd house so we applied for it.
They said we couldn't get approved on the lesser amount because Matt had changed jobs and wasn't over his "probationary period".
Matt get's his probationary period wavered.
We go through with the application- settlement was meant to be Friday 28th July, then Wednesday 2nd August and then we honestly thought today at 3.30pm we would get the keys, but noooo the stupid f*ckheads reckon they need another day!

Like F*ck!

I've told the solicitor to tell them that we have a removalist truck coming at 4.30pm today to move our stuff in and too bad. Not true but I'm so sick and f*cking tired of them f*cking up.

When we get the chance we are DEFINATLEY changing banks...

**Deep Breath**
